^ONCE THE REQUEST IS COMPLETED, IT SHOULD BE ^Q^A'D BY THE ^SYSTEM
^QUALITY ^CONTROLLER.  ^IN THE EVENT THAT THERE IS NO ^SYSTEM ^QUALITY
^CONTROLLER ON A PARTICULAR SHIFT, THE REQUEST SHOULD BE ^Q^A'D BY
SOMEONE OTHER THAN THE ^OPERATOR WHO PERFORMED THE JOB.  ^IT IS
THE <QA PERSON'S RESPONSIBILITY TO ENSURE THAT THE JOB WAS COMPLETED
CORRECTLY.  ^THE REQUEST IS THEN SIGNED OFF, FILED, AND A <BATCH
<COMPLETION <FORM SENT.  (^SEE <"ONTYME <BATCH <RUN <COMPLETION" ON
^PAGE 15.)
